---
description: Apply uv package manager patterns. Use when managing dependencies or running project commands.
globs: pyproject.toml, uv.lock
alwaysApply: false
---

Package Management:
- Use `uv add <pkg>` to add dependencies
- Use `uv add --dev <pkg>` for dev dependencies
- Use `uv sync` to install all dependencies
- Use `uv run <cmd>` to run commands in the venv

Build:
- Build system: `hatchling`
- Package layout: `src/` layout with `src/septeo_scaffolder/`
- Entry point: `[project.scripts]` in `pyproject.toml`

Avoid:
- `pip install` directly — use `uv add`
- Manual venv management — `uv` handles it
- Editing `uv.lock` manually
